<p>Trees</p>
<p>A tree is a kind of ADT that stores data, much like a queue, a linked list, or a stack. </p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Advantages of using a tree, as opposed to a linked list:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Fast search/removal times (O(log(n))) in a binary search tree</li>
  <li>Fast get-min-element in a min-heap ordered tree (O(1))</li>
</ul>
<p>Disadvantages of using a tree:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Requires more memory per item (sizeof item, left pointer, right pointer)</li>
  <li>Can be time-consuming to keep rebalancing the tree</li>
</ul>
